quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  4,148,"God does not love evil talk in public unless it is by some who has been injured thereby. God is Alert, Aware"
  4,149,"Whether you reveal any good or hide it, or pardon any evil, God is Pardoning, Capable"
  4,150,"Those who disbelieve in God and His messengers, and want to distinguish between God and His messengers, and say: Â´We believe in some and disbelieve in others;\" wanting to adopt a course in between"
  4,151,are really disbelievers. We have reserved humiliating torment for disbelievers
  4,152,"Those who believe in God and His messengers, and not single out any one of them [especially], will be given their earnings. God is Forgiving, Merciful"
  4,153,"The People of the Book ask you to have a book sent down from Heaven for them. They asked Moses for something even greater than that, and said: \"Show us God directly.\" The Thunderbolt caught them in wrongdoing. Then they adopted the Calf even after explanations had come to them. We still pardoned that, and gave Moses clear authority"
  4,154,"We raised the Mountain up over them as their charter, and told them: \"Enter the while on your knees.\" We told them [further]: \"Do not go too far on Sabbath,\" and made a solemn pledge with them"